        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:12PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Macedonia, or near
Hiawassee, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hiawassee, Young Harris, Blue Mountain Shelter, Brasstown Bald, Tate
City, Macedonia, Plum Orchard Gap Shelter, Titus, and Mountain Scene.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
